            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are several of the most prominent renewable energy trends in 2026, drawn from recent insights:\n\n1. **Energy Storage Advances**  \n   - Significant developments in battery technologies, including **next-generation lithium-silicon and sodium-ion batteries** and **long-duration energy storage (LDES)**, are addressing the intermittency of renewable sources like wind and solar. This enables clean energy availability around the clock [RatedPower](https://www.renewableenergymagazine.com/panorama/ratedpower-publishes-2026-global-renewable-energy-trends-20260227).\n\n2. **Breakthroughs in Solar Technology**  \n   - **Perovskite solar cells** are increasingly hitting commercial markets, offering higher efficiency (above 30%) and reduced costs. Additionally, **floating solar farms** are being deployed globally, particularly in Asia and Europe [Renewable Energy Conference](https://www.renewableenergyconference.org/blog/trends-in-renewable-energy-2026.html).\n\n3. **Green Hydrogen Expansion**  \n   - For the first time, green hydrogen is moving beyond conceptual stages. Global hydrogen hubs are scaling up, supported by cost reductions in electrolyzers and national hydrogen strategies. This trend aids the decarbonization of heavy industries like steel and cement [Renewable Energy Conference](https://www.renewableenergyconference.org/blog/trends-in-renewable-energy-2026.html).\n\n4. **Offshore Wind Growth**  \n   - **Floating offshore wind farms** are unlocking wind energy potential in deeper waters. Key expansion is occurring in regions like the North Sea and U.S. East Coast [Renewable Energy Conference](https://www.renewableenergyconference.org/blog/trends-in-renewable-energy-2026.html).\n\n5. **Digital and AI Technologies in Energy**  \n   - Integration of **artificial intelligence (AI)** into smart grids and energy systems is optimizing operations. AI is enabling real-time demand response and predictive analytics, which improve grid management and energy forecasting [StartUs Insights](https://www.startus-insights.com/innovators-guide/renewable-energy-trends/).\n\n6. **Hybrid and Solar-Plus-Storage Projects**  \n   - Hybrid systems combining solar, energy storage, and other renewable sources have become increasingly popular. Hybrid solar-plus-storage projects grew from 12% in 2024 to 20% in 2025. AC-coupled Battery Energy Storage Systems (BESS) are leading this space [Enverus via PR Newswire](https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/ratedpower-publishes-2026-global-renewable-energy-trends-report-as-ai-storage-and-grid-constraints-redefine-market-dynamics-302698607.html).\n\n7. **Policy and Market Shifts**  \n   - Shifting renewable energy policies—such as shortening tax incentive windows and adapting compliance requirements—are accelerating project implementation timelines. However, supply chain pressures, grid constraints, and permitting remain barriers [Deloitte Insights](https://www.deloitte.com/us/en/insights/industry/renewable-energy/renewable-energy-industry-outlook.html).\n\nThese trends demonstrate rapid innovation and deployment, but they are accompanied by challenges such as grid saturation, infrastructure limitations, and viability under short-term policy changes. For further insights about each trend, check the provided sources for detailed information.",
